The paper deals with medical image registration using deep learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks for registration also suggests that the paper could belong to machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper specifically deals with medical images, which could also place it in the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of cycle consistency in the proposed method suggests that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
